title: For Sale/Trade:  CZ75 transitional with Vortex Viper
postcontent: If you're not super familiar with CZs, this is a "transitional" model CZ75, which is fairly rare, and pretty cool. When CZ was moving from the original 75 to the 75B, the transitional models were basically 75Bs without the firing pin block and a very, very nice trigger. So, the advantages of the "pre-B" but it takes "B" parts and magazines, which are far cheaper and easier to find.I replaced the original worn barrel bushing with a Cajun Gunworks precision bushing ($60), and replaced all of the springs with new factory weight springs. The original plastic grips were also badly chipped, so I put on new factory CZ rubber grip panels.The front sight is factory, with fresh paint in the contrast markings, and the read sight has been replaced with a CGW red dot mount($50), and fitted with a Vortex Viper red dot ($180). I still have the factory steel rear sight, which I will be including with the gun.I was originally going to cerakote it (and you can too, I recommend Gun Envy here in Columbus - fantastic work and good prices), but decided to leave it as a "sleeper" with the original finish. It's exceptionally accurate, and feeds reliably from factory mags, Mec-Gar replacements (it does come with a brand new Mec-Gar), and also a few cheap Turkish clone magazines one of my buddies has.I may take cash for the right offer, but much prefer a trade. No long guns, bows, black powder, etc - I'm looking for a Sig other than the SP2022, preferably a P228, but I'm open to other Sigs or other interesting handguns. 9mm, please!
